<DOC><DOCNO> AP890504-0101 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-04-89 1213EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Korea-Ship     05-04 0179</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Korea-Ship,0185</SECOND><HEAD>Navy Ships Foil Alleged Communist Attempt To Seize Fishing Boat</HEAD><DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   South Korean navy ships on Thursdayfoiled an apparent North Korean attempt to seize a South Koreanfishing boat near the western sea border, the Defense Ministry said.   A North Korean naval craft tried to seize the 23-ton Samjin-hooperating in the area, the ministry said.   The North Korean ship retreated to the north when South Koreannavy ships chased it, the ministry said.   North Korea has seized South Korean fishing boats near thewestern sea border, but returned most of them.   In January, two South Korean fishing boats with 22 crewmen onboard were seized in the area. The ships and all their crewmen werereturned two weeks later.   According to government figures, North Korea has seized 295South Korean fishing boats since 1945.   North Korea's Korean Central News Agency accused South Korea ofsending a warship into North Korean waters off the west coast, butsaid it fled south when a North Korean patrol boat arrived at thescene.</TEXT></DOC>